This is a pure python webserver implementation using pythons BaseHTTPServer.

Start by python MyLittlePythonServer.py (--bind, --port, --protocol)

Sample:
for ipv4
python MyLittlePythonServer.py

for ipv6 (not tested)
python MyLittlePythonServer.py --protocol ipv6

all sample
python MyLittlePythonServer.py --bind 10.0.0.1 --port 8118 --protocol ipv4

If you dont supply a ip it defaults to 127.0.0.1.
If you dont supply a port it defaults to 80.
If you dont supply a protocol it defaults to ipv4.

NOTE: Python script made in part by findings on the net and pieced together with some edits.
